1. Pull the latest changes with rebase: git pull --rebase origin main
2. Add your changes: git add .
3. Commit your changes: git commit -m "Your descriptive message"
4. Push your changes: git push origin main
5. Revert the last commit if needed: git reset --hard HEAD~1
6. Force-push after resetting: git push origin main --force
7. Cherry-pick a specific commit: git cherry-pick <commit-hash> ("Note: This applies a single commit from elsewhere onto your current branch, useful for bringing in individual changes without merging the whole branch.")


##############################################
